Title: Http1.1 Upload traffic with LFS(Data trickling disabled) with DLP with origin having < 6s as idle connection timeout with feature flag
Section: ENG-332152:re-establish back connection on timeout errors
Section Description:
https://netskope.atlassian.net/browse/ENG-332152

The issue is seen due to connection reuse and shorter server timeout (in this case 6 secs). The browser re-uses existing connection to send upload request, if nsproxy holds upload for content inspection for more than 6 secs then server side times out and closes the connection. We need to enhance nsproxy to handle connection reuse use-case to fix the issue. 

If back connection is closed because of timeout then nsproxy should open a new back connection to continue with the transaction.
Section Hierarchy: Datapath(CASB & SWG) - India QE > SWG/N4W/Altos > ENG-332152:re-establish back connection on timeout errors
